    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The home circle should be regarded as a sacred place, a symbol of heaven, a mirror in which to reflect ourselves. Friends and acquaintances we may have, but in the home life they are not to meddle. A strong sense of proprietorship should be felt, giving a sense of ease, restfulness, trust.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">2<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 17, 1895\" data-link=\"14060.5397001\">Letter 17, 1895</span>.</span></a></sup>",
