    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 178.3 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Parents should be careful not to allow the spirit of dissension to creep into the home; for this is one of Satan&apos;s agents to make his impression on the character. If parents will strive for unity in the home by inculcating the principles that governed the life of Christ, dissension will be driven out, and unity and love will abide there. Parents and children will partake of the gift of the Holy Spirit.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">5<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Ms 53, 1912\" data-link=\"14075.10797001\">Manuscript 53, 1912</span>.</span></a></sup>",
