    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Although trials may arise in the married life, the husband and the wife are to keep their souls in the love of <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"179\"></span> God. The father should look upon the mother of his children as one deserving of all kindness, tenderness, and sympathy.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">7<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 198, 1901\" data-link=\"14066.10165001\">Letter 198, 1901</span>.</span></a></sup>",
